A popular Nigerian cleric, Pastor Adewale Giwa, has disclosed that the wrath of God will visit those behind the doldrums and quagmire facing Nigeria. While disclosing that politicians who have been oppressing Nigerians will be crushed by God in 2022, the foremost cleric said none of them will be spared. Pastor Giwa, who is the Senior Pastor of the Awaiting the Second Coming of Jesus Christ Ministry, Akure, Ondo State, stated this in his New Year message to Nigerians and the country. In the message made available to DAILY POST, the pastor who said God will rise for Nigerians in 2022 disclosed that God gave him the revelation to deliver to the people. While disclosing in the revelation that God will not only be ruthless with the political oppressors but will also be punished for their inequalities. According to Pastor Giwa, 2022 will be a year of turnaround for Nigerians, emphasising that those responsible for the nation’s current woes will not escape the anger of God. “It is the promise of God that the political oppressors of Nigeria shall remain no more. God is rising for the sake of His true people. “Nigerians will live to see their downfall. God says He will punish them for their iniquities and crush them all. This promise shall not fail, write it down.” The cleric urged Nigerians to pray for the deliverance of the country from the shackles of oppression and suffering. According to him, Nigeria needs leaders with vision and mission that will bring rapid transformation to the country.